HEADWORD: Magnifical
<hw>Mag*nif"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>magnificus</ets>;
<ets>magnus</ets> great + <ets>facere</ets> to make: cf. F.
<ets>magnifique</ets>. See <er>Magnitude</er>, <er>Fact</er>. and cf.
<er>Magnificent</er>.]</ety> <def>Grand; splendid; illustrious;
magnificent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>1 Chron. xxii. 5.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Thy <xex>magnific</xex> deeds.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> --
